Proposed Structural & Animation Changes:

### 1. Global Navigation & Animations
- **Floating "Island" Bottom Nav:** Instead of a bar stuck to the bottom edge, we will create a pill-shaped, floating "Dynamic Island" style navigation bar that hovers slightly above the bottom.
- **Page Transitions:** Implement full fade-in and slight scale-up animations when navigating between pages (Dashboard <-> Shipments) to make routing feel instantaneous and fluid.

### 2. The Dashboard (Redesigned)
- **Floating Search Bar:** Move the "Track Shipment" input to a floating, rounded search bar at the very top of the screen (overlapping the sky gradient) for maximum efficiency.
- **Asymmetrical Hero Section:** Instead of a flat gradient block, the airplane section will have a smooth, sweeping curved bottom edge.
- **Circular Activity Rings:** Replace the standard rectangular cards with a horizontal scrolling row of minimalist "Active Shipment" rings (similar to fitness trackers) that give a quick visual of progress.

### 3. My Shipments (Redesigned)
- **Fluid Segmented Control:** Replace the basic tab pills with an iOS-style fluid segmented control where a highlighted bubble smoothly slides behind the selected text.
- **Timeline-based Cards:** Instead of bulky cards with "From/To" boxes, we will use a vertical timeline design for each card. A sleek line connects the origin dot to the destination dot, with the status hovering gracefully above it.
- **Hover/Active States:** When pressing a shipment card, it will slightly shrink (scale down) and fade, giving immediate tactile feedback.

### 4. Sidebar (Redesigned)
- **Morphing Shapes:** The sidebar won't just slide in as a hard rectangle; it will slide in with a soft, curved right edge that straightens out, making the transition feel organic.
- **Staggered Fade-in:** When the sidebar opens, the menu items won't just appear—they will stagger-fade in one by one from top to bottom.
